obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (31806)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. The words "and Acceding States of India" omitted by the A.O. 1950.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00017_194908_1517807325444&sectionId=31806&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00017_194908_1517807325444
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Seaward Artillery Practice`
  line `Act, 1949.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to all the States ^2* * * which have a sea coast and applies also to, and to persons on, any`
  line `vessel which is registered in India or which belongs to any person domiciled in India, wherever it may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (31807)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Interpretation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Omitted by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 3) Order, 1956.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00017_194908_1517807325444&sectionId=31807&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00017_194908_1517807325444
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `(a) "notified area" means any part of the area of the sea and the shores adjoining that area which`
  line `may be specified in this behalf by notification under section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) "seaward artillery practice" means artillery practice or coastal firing towards the sea, whether`
  line `within or beyond the territorial waters and includes air armament practice;`
  line
  line `(d) "vessel" includes any ship, boat, country craft or any other description of vessel.`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (31808)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power of Central Government to authorise seaward artillery practice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1973, s. 2, for section 3 (w.e.f. 21-1-1978).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00017_194908_1517807325444&sectionId=31808&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00017_194908_1517807325444
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1[3. Power of Central Government to authorise seaward artillery practice.--(1) The Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, authorise the carrying out of seaward artillery`
  line `practice over such area and during such period or periods as may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that there shall be an interval of at least fourteen days between the date of publication of`
  line `such notification in the Official Gazette and the date of carrying out of seaward artillery practice.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall, as soon as may be, after the publication of a notification under`
  line `sub-section (1), cause the substance thereof to be published--`
  line
  line `(a) in some newspaper circulating in, and in the language commonly understood in, the area`
  line `specified in the notification; and`
  line
  line `(b) in such other manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) If any question arises whether the substance of a notification under sub-section (1) was published`
  line `as required by sub-section (2), a certificate by the Collector of the district in which the notified area is`
  line `situate that the substance of the notification was so published, shall be conclusive.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_a:
  sectionId (31809)
  sectionNo 3A
  orderNo 4
  title `Power to delegate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1973, s. 2, for section 3 (w.e.f. 21-1-1978).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00017_194908_1517807325444&sectionId=31809&sectionno=3A&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00017_194908_1517807325444
obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[3A. Power to delegate.--The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct`
  line `that the power to issue notification under section 3 shall, subject to such conditions, if any, as may be`
  line `specified in the notification, be exercisable also by such State Government as may be specified therein.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (31810)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 5
  title `Powers exercisable for purposes of seaward artillery practice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00017_194908_1517807325444&sectionId=31810&sectionno=4&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00017_194908_1517807325444
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) After a notification under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 3 has been issued, such persons as are included in the forces engaged in`
  line `seaward artillery practice may within the notified area and during the period or periods specified in the`
  line notification--
  line
  line `(a) give directions prohibiting or restricting the use of the notified area or any part thereof`
  line `including the use of any part of the area of the sea by any vessel, and take such further measures as`
  line `may be necessary to ensure that no unauthorised person enters, passes over or remains in the notified`
  line `area or part thereof, as the case may be, during such practice, and`
  line
  line `(b) carry out seaward artillery practice with lethal missiles.`
  line
  line `(2) The Officer Commanding the forces engaged in any such practice may declare any portion of the`
  line `notified area to be a danger zone, and thereupon the Collector shall, on application made to him by the`
  line `Officer Commanding the forces engaged in the practice, prohibit the entry into and secure, with the`
  line `assistance of the naval or military authorities concerned, the removal from such danger zone of any`
  line `person, property or vessel during the times when the discharge of lethal missiles is taking place or there is`
  line `danger to life or property.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (31811)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title Compensation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00017_194908_1517807325444&sectionId=31811&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00017_194908_1517807325444
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Where by reason of a notification issued under section 3 the carrying out of`
  line `seaward artillery practice is authorised in any notified area, compensation shall be payable for any`
  line `damage to person or property or interference with rights or privileges arising from such practice,`
  line `including expenses reasonably incurred in protecting person, property, rights or privileges.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (31812)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Method of assessing compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00017_194908_1517807325444&sectionId=31812&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00017_194908_1517807325444
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of determining the amount of any`
  line `compensation payable under section 5, the Collector of the district in which any notified area is situate`
  line `shall depute one or more Revenue Officers to accompany the forces engaged in the practice.`
  line
  line `(2) The Revenue Officer so deputed shall consider all claims for compensation under section 5 and`
  line `determine, on local investigation and after affording the claimant an opportunity of being heard, the`
  line `amount of compensation, if any, which shall be awarded in each case; and shall disburse on the spot to the`
  line `claimant compensation so determined as payable.`
  line
  line `(3) Compensation payable under sub-section (2) shall include compensation for the removal from any`
  line `portion of a notified area declared to be a danger zone of any person, property or vessel and for any`
  line `damage sustained in the course of any such removal. The compensation for removal will be disbursed on`
  line `the spot at not less than the minimum prescribed rates before the removal is enforced.`
  line
  line `(4) Any claimant dissatisfied with the refusal of the Revenue Officer to award him compensation or`
  line `with the amount of compensation awarded to him by the Revenue Officer, may, at any time within one`
  line `month of the communication to him of the decision of the Revenue Officer, prefer an appeal to the`
  line `Collector against the decision.`
  line
  line `(5) The decision of the Collector on such appeal shall be final and no suit shall lie in any civil Court`
  line `in respect of any matter decided by the Collector under this section.`
  line
  line `(6) No fee shall be charged in connection with any claim, notice, appeal, application or document`
  line `filed before the Revenue Officer or the Collector under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (31813)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title Offences.
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00017_194908_1517807325444&sectionId=31813&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00017_194908_1517807325444
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `If within a notified area and during any period specified in a notification issued under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 3, any person--`
  line
  line `(a) wilfully obstructs or interferes with the carrying out of seaward artillery practice, or`
  line
  line `(b) without due authority enters or remains in any camp, or`
  line
  line `(c) without due authority enters or remains in any area declared to be a danger zone at a time`
  line `when entry thereto is prohibited, or`
  line
  line `(d) without due authority interferes with any flag or mark or target or buoy or any apparatus used`
  line `for the purposes of seaward artillery practice,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with fine which may extend to twenty rupees or with imprisonment which may extend`
  line `to fifteen days, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (31814)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Protection of action taken under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00017_194908_1517807325444&sectionId=31814&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00017_194908_1517807325444
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against any person for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance`
  line `of this Act or any rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) Except as otherwise provided in this Act, no suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the`
  line `Central Government or the State Government in respect of any damage caused or likely to be caused by`
  line `anything in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act or any rules made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (31815)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1973, s. 3, for section 9 (w.e.f. 21-1-1978).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00017_194908_1517807325444&sectionId=31815&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00017_194908_1517807325444
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `^1[9.Power to make rules.--(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for giving effect to the provisions of this Act and different rules may be made for different`
  line `States or for different areas thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which the substance of a notification under section 3 may be published;`
  line
  line `(b) regulating the use under this Act of the notified area for seaward artillery practice in such`
  line `manner as to secure the public against danger, and to enable the practice to be carried out with the`
  line `minimum inconvenience to the inhabitants of the area affected;`
  line
  line `(c) the minimum rates at which compensation shall be payable under sub-section (3) of section 6,`
  line `and generally regarding the making of claims for compensation, the procedure to be followed by the`
  line `authorities granting the compensation, the expeditious settlement of claims and the filling of appeals`
  line `from original awards of compensation;`
  line
  line `(d) the principles to be followed in assessing the amount of compensation to be awarded under`
  line `this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
